            "name": "Information and integration assistance",
            "description": "<p><span style=\"color: rgb(93,93,93);\">The Orange House is situated in the center of Athens and it constitutes a multicenter which includes a variety of subservices targeted to the population of refugees and migrants of Athens. </span></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<ul>\n<li>English and Greek language courses for adults</li>\n<li>Orange House - Professional trainings (hairdresser/barber, cook...)</li>\n<li>Orange House - Multicenter CV workshops</li>\n<li>Legal service for asylum seekers</li>\n<li>Social support services Zaatar</li>\n<li>Ecofriendly and social restaurant training and employing refugees and asylum-seekers : Tastes of Damascus</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<h3>Additional Information</h3>\n<p>The Greek lessons are held through Zoom. Those interested to register can send whatsapp messages to: +30 694 067 1666.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Send a message on Facebook for more information.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Location</h3>\n<p>Athens.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Please note, for safety reasons, <strong>we do not publish our location online</strong>. If you need to find our building in Athens, please use the contact form below to reach out to our team directly!</p>\n<p>For urgent needs, you can reach <strong>The Orange House by phone at +30 694 0671666.</strong></p>\n",
