            "description": "<p>CRWI Diotima offers legal aid for men and boys (age 16 and over) who have experienced gender-based violence:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Information about seeking asylum and your rights</li>\n<li>Individual counseling</li>\n<li>Legal aid and representation during the asylum process</li>\n<li>Representation in court for criminal and civil cases</li>\n</ul>\n<p>They also offer additional support:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Information and referrals</li>\n<li>One-on-one assistance, including going with you to public and local services such as health, security, and social care services</li>\n<li>Referrals to shelters</li>\n<li>Continued check-ins to be sure you are able to get the help you need</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Gender-based violence includes sexual violence or exploitation, or physical or psychological violence due to your sexual orientation.</p>\n<h3>Additional Information</h3>\n<p><br></p>\n<h3>Email CRWI Diotima to make an appointment.Location</h3>\n<p>Athens</p>\n<h3>Address</h3>\n<p>Athens</p>\n<h3>Address in Local Language</h3>\n<p>Αθηνα</p>\n",
