            "language": "en",
            "name": "Food and non-food items distribution",
            "description": "<p>Provision of food (canned/dry goods, fresh produce on availability) and non-food items (hygiene products, homelessness support items). Frequency depends on availability.</p>\n<p>Interested persons are required to text the Emantes’ Support Line (Monday to Friday 09:00 – 17:00, +306971693446). Distribution depends on availability and is preceded by an assessment of needs.</p>\n<p>Languages spoken: Greek English French Farsi/Dari Arabic Kurmanji Urdu Lingala Somali Turkish Bengali Pashto Sorani (automatic translation through the Support Line)</p>\n<p>Address: Confidential</p>\n<p>Phone Number +302103802317 Greek, English</p>\n<p>Whatsapp Number: +306971693446 (The Support Line operates with automatic translation for languages other than Greek and English.)</p>\n<p>Emails:&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>info.emantes@gmail.com (general enquiries),&nbsp;</li>\n<li>emantes.socialservice@gmail.com (social service)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Accessibility &amp; Additional Information</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>This service is closed on public holidays YES</li>\n<li>Is an appointment required? YES (phone, WhatsApp, Viber, Facebook, etc.)</li>\n<li>Eligibility for services: LGBTQIA+ asylum seeker/refugee/migrant adults (over 18 years old)&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Are services available by referral only? NO - Interested persons are required to text the Emantes’ Support Line (Monday to Friday 09:00 – 17:00, +306971693446) themselves</li>\n<li>The entrance to this location has a ramp YES</li>\n<li>This location has an elevator YES</li>\n<li>This location has female staff YES</li>\n<li>This location has separate bathrooms for men and women NO</li>\n<li>All Services Listed Are Free of Charge YES</li>\n</ul>\n",
