            "language": "en",
            "name": "Breastfeeding support program RIC Lesvos camp",
            "description": "<p><span style=\"color: black;\">Starfish in partnership with MAM Beyond Borders is carrying out a breastfeeding support initiative in the RIC Mavrovouni, Lesvos. The program is aimed at protecting and promoting breastfeeding, and supports a female-focused network for community support within the camp, with group meetings during the pregnancy and one to one consultations after the delivery. The program focuses on supporting pregnant women, and breastfeeding mothers and infants up to 1-year-old, priority is given to new-borns. Currently, antenatal meetings are held twice a week in a women-only space nearby the RIC. Starfish and MAM are starting to support pregnant women and new mothers also living in Mytilene</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong>Additional Information</strong></p><p><span style=\"color: black;\">Whether a referral is needed to access the specific service y/n: Yes (sessions are open to all but outreach is done by volunteers to identify pregnant and lactating women in the camp and then a ticketing system is used to manage the number of people per session)</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong>Location</strong></p><p>Lesvos</p><p><strong>Address</strong></p><p>Vournazon 25,</p><p>RIC Lesvos camp Mytilene 81100</p>",
